Before this quickly devolves into a Mac Smullen fan account (which, let’s be honest - it already has) let’s get one fact out of the way. 

I’ve never been in love before. 

I’ve never been in love and I’ve never felt love as sincere and honest and without strings or ulterior motives. I have never had a partner that is also my best friend and my lover and then my best friend again (forever and ever, amen.) I have never met someone who excites me daily and inspires me to do what I must to become the woman I want to be.

I am so proud of his recent successes, but even more the tenacity it took to make them happen. His dogged belief in the craft, and that the truth will always be in the work.

Thank you David Cronenberg and “Night Film” and Robert Eggers for making “The Lighthouse.” Thank you to the friend I don’t remember who had a birthday party that night. Thank you Ralph Fiennes for acting in “Spider.” Thank you to whomever made that awful movie “Knives & Skin.” Thank you Film Noir and Lake Street and my tiny old apartment where we ate pancakes and watched “Trust.”

I love you, I love you. 

Happy Valentines x

@theviolentbearitaway

Ten years is a long time, Jeremy. I’m running out of pictures where I don’t look terrible. You died at home and nobody ever told me how it happened, but we both know I know and wish that I didn’t.

Every year I try to celebrate your birthday but last year I forgot. I’d been preparing, but life got in the way - a phrase that now feels both morbidly ironic and unnecessarily cruel.

I’d wanted to talk about our time together - like the way we used to sleep in the same bed & never touch - but we weren’t together very long. I met you in 2009 and by 2010 you were gone from my life, but not out of my brain or my body. 

After you gave me my first oxy and I’d had to wear dark sunglasses from spinning all night. After your mother handed me a fist full of pills because I’d had a rough day on set. When you stopped coming home and moved out without saying goodbye. 

How many addiction stories begin and end with someone’s mother trying to help, while hurting them both at the same time?

When I googled your name to see if there was anyone else thinking about you today, I reread her death notice. I wasn’t able to find yours.

Jeremy Badr, 1988 - 2016

I love making pictures and I’ve always loved making pictures. But it can be difficult as a stylist to feel like you’re in control of the images you make. I became jealous last year, perhaps spiteful even, of those who are able to create without constraint. So I set up a studio in my kitchen and started shooting again.

Pictures are perfect because nothing outside the frame matters. They are only imprints of moments left behind. You don’t know there are unwashed dishes in my sink. You shouldn’t care. 

And let’s be honest - nothing is more beautiful than when it is manipulated by light & color. Everyone knows that.
